While IE9 is not a supported browser, there is [a very easy workaround|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONF-22060] to make Confluence usable again. This workaround was included in Confluence 3.5.2 (and consequently in Studio, which is running 3.5.3). The workaround is to include this meta tag as the first tag in <head>:

{code:html}
<meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=8">
{code}

Unfortunately Studio breaks this workaround:

{code:html}
<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/strict.dtd">
<html>
<head>
  <title>Home - Support IRC Bot - Confluence</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/wiki/s/en/2155/2/103.6/_/download/resources/com.atlassian.studio.static:studio_resources/css/navbar.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="https://labs.atlassian.com/plugins/servlet/studio/dynamiccss/studio-colors-css.css">
  <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=8">
{code}

Since this meta tag needs to be [the first tag in the head section|http://evolpin.wordpress.com/2011/02/25/ie9-compatibility-and-the-meta-tag/], IE9 fails to trigger IE8 compatibility mode. In the console it reports:
{noformat}
HTML1115: X-UA-Compatible META tag ('IE=EmulateIE8′) ignored because document mode is already finalized.
{noformat}

The workaround is for IE9 users to manually turn on compatibility mode using [these instructions from Microsoft|http://support.microsoft.com/kb/956197#1].

